## 6. 🧩 COMPONENT PATTERNS

### Cards vs Lists
- **No cards**. The system uses **horizontal list rows** throughout.
- Even the detail view is a linear reading layout, not a card grid.
- The only "surface" with a box is the edit modal bottom sheet.

### Buttons

| Class | Style | Used For |
|---|---|---|
| `.btn-primary` | Filled `--bg-active`, 1px border | Primary CTAs (Start Over, etc.) |
| `.btn-ghost` | Transparent, 1px `--border-default` | Secondary actions, Cancel |
| `.btn-ghost-danger` | Transparent, 1px `#3a2222`, text `#b05252` | Delete/destructive |
| `.btn-icon` | Icon-only 28×28 square, no border | Header icon buttons |
| `.btn-icon-sm` | Icon-only 22×22 | Inline icon action (small) |
| `.btn-add` | Small text + icon, `--border-default` | Add item buttons in section headers |
| `.btn-add-group` | Full-width dashed border | Add skill group |
| `.btn-copy` | Text + icon, `--accent` color | Copy URL in share panel |
| `.link-btn` | Inline text, `--accent` color, no border | Empty state links |
| `.row-action-btn` | 24×24 invisible, hover reveals color | Edit/delete on rows |
| `.identity-edit-btn` | 28×28, transparent border, hover shows | Profile edit trigger |
| `.tab-btn` | Flex column, fill tab bar slot | Mobile nav tabs |

> **Pattern**: No button has a visible background unless it's `.btn-primary`. All others are ghost or icon-only.

### Inputs & Forms

| Element | Style |
|---|---|
| `input`, `textarea` | `--bg-input`, 1px `--border-default`, focus → `--border-accent` |
| `.edit-input` | Same, `--sp-2 --sp-3` padding, 13px font |
| `.edit-textarea` | Same as edit-input, resizable vertically |
| `.lock-input` | Same pattern, slightly different padding |
| `.onboarding-textarea` | Fixed 100px height, 13px, same background pattern |

> All inputs follow the exact same visual pattern. Very consistent.

### Modals
- **Edit modal**: bottom-sheet style (`align-items: flex-end`), slide-up animation, max 640px, 85vh max-height
- **Share modal**: same overlay + sheet, narrower (max 380px), centered content inside
- **Password modal**: same overlay + sheet pattern
- All modals use `rgba(0,0,0,0.6)` scrim, `fadeIn 160ms` backdrop, `slideUpModal 220ms cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)` content

### Tags
- `.tag`: `--bg-surface`, 1px `--border-default`, 11px text, `--text-secondary`, 3px 8px padding
- Flat, small, no radius
- Used in detail views for tech stacks, skills

### Rows / Lists
- `.section-row` — overview navigation rows (clickable, navigate forward)
- `.item-row` — section content rows (clickable to detail + edit/delete actions)  
- `.link-row` — links section rows (anchor tags)
- All rows: `border-bottom: 1px --border-subtle`, `padding: --sp-4 0`, no background
- First row gets `border-top` for visual enclosure

### Overlays (Layers)
- Level 0: `.overview-wrap` (base content)
- Level 1: `.section-overlay` (z-index: 50) — slides over overview
- Level 2: `.detail-overlay` (z-index: 100) — slides over section
- Edit: `.edit-overlay` (z-index: 500)
- Mobile: `.mobile-tab-bar` (z-index: 500)
- Fullscreen: `.fullscreen-center` (z-index: 300) — auth/onboarding

---

## 7. 🧭 NAVIGATION MODEL

### Model Type: **Progressive Disclosure / Flow-Based**

No sidebar. No persistent tabs on desktop. Three levels of depth:

```
Level 0 — Overview (identity + section menu)
  ↓ tap Section Row
Level 1 — Section View (list of items for that section)
  ↓ tap Item Row
Level 2 — Detail View (full reading view for one item)
```

Back navigation via:
- Header breadcrumb (click "MyProfile" → home, click section name → one level back)
- Header back chevron (`ChevronLeft`) — visible on mobile when not at home
- `animBack()` function handles exit animation before actual navigation

**Mobile** (≤640px) adds a persistent **bottom tab bar** `{Home, Share, Settings}` that replaces modals with inline tab views.

**Desktop** exposes share/lock/reset in the header-right area.

---

## 8. 🎬 INTERACTION SYSTEM

### Animation Keyframes

| Name | Effect | Duration | Easing |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fadeIn` | Opacity 0→1 | 200ms | `ease` |
| `overviewIn` | Fade + translateY(10→0) | 260ms | `ease` |
| `sectionIn` | translateX(32→0) + fade | 220ms | `cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)` |
| `sectionOut` | translateX(0→40) + fade | 160ms | `ease` |
| `detailIn` | translateY(14→0) + scale(0.985→1) | 240ms | `cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)` |
| `detailOut` | translateY(0→10) + scale(1→0.99) | 140ms | `ease` |
| `slideUpModal` | translateY(40→0) + fade | 220ms | `cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)` |
| `lockShake` | ±8px horizontal shake | 450ms | `ease` |
| `parseProgress` | Width 0→100% | 1.8s | `ease-in-out` |

### Transition Tokens

| Token | Value | Used In |
|---|---|---|
| `--transition` | `150ms ease` | Default: colors, backgrounds, borders |
| `--transition-slow` | `220ms ease` | Defined, not explicitly referenced in any class |

### Hover Behaviors

| Element | Hover Effect |
|---|---|
| `.section-row:hover .section-row__label` | Color → `--text-primary` |
| `.section-row:hover .section-row__arrow` | Color → `--accent`, translateX(+3px) |
| `.item-row:hover .item-row__title` | Color → `--text-primary` |
| `.item-row:hover .item-row__arrow` | Color → `--accent`, translateX(+3px) |
| `.item-row:hover .item-row__actions` | opacity 0 → 1 (reveal edit/delete) |
| `.link-row:hover .link-row__name` | Color → `--text-primary` |
| `.btn-icon:hover` | Color → `--text-secondary` |
| `.btn-ghost:hover` | Background → `--bg-hover`, border → `--border-accent` |
| `.btn-ghost-danger:hover` | Background dim red, border/text → `#e05252` |
| `.detail-link-btn:hover` | Background → `--accent-dim`, border → `--accent` |
| `.drop-zone:hover` | Background → `--bg-hover`, border → `--accent` |
| `.pwd-menu-item:hover` | Background → `--bg-hover`, border/text upgrades |
| `.tab-btn:active` | Opacity → 0.4 (no hover state on mobile) |

---

## 9. ⚠️ INCONSISTENCIES

### Duplicate Styles / Token Violations

| Issue | Detail |
|---|---|
| `--transition-slow` defined, never used | Token `220ms ease` declared in `:root` but zero references |
| `--radius-sm (1px)` defined, never used | Radius token declared but no selector applies it |
| `--text-inverse` defined, never used | Color token declared with no usage in the codebase |
| `#141414` hardcoded in `.edit-modal` | Should be `var(--bg-input)` |
| `#111111` hardcoded in `.share-qr` | Should be `var(--bg-surface)` |
| `#b8956a` hardcoded in `.tab-btn--active::before` | Should be `var(--accent)` |
| `#ffffff` hardcoded in `.tab-btn--active` | No token for white — should be `--text-primary` or a new token |
| `rgba(12,12,12,0.98)` in mobile tab bar | Near-duplicate of `--bg-base` with opacity, no token |
| `rgba(0,0,0,0.6)` overlay scrim | Hardcoded, no token |

### Raw Pixel Values That Should Be Tokens

| Value | Location | Suggested Token |
|---|---|---|
| `88px` | Mobile content padding-bottom | `--tab-bar-clear` |
| `3px` | Row body gaps | `--sp-0.75` or use `--sp-1-` |
| `6px` | Detail link btn padding | Between `--sp-1` and `--sp-2` |
| `14px` | Mobile row padding | Between `--sp-3` and `--sp-4`, or same as `--sp-3.5` |

### Structural Issues

| Issue | Detail |
|---|---|
| No error/success color tokens | `#e05252`, `#b05252`, `#3a2222`, `#5aba8a` all hardcoded many times |
| `.section-heading` defined twice | Lines 158–165 and lines 988–994 in `components.css` — second definition overwrites the margin-bottom of the first |
| `.item-row` defined twice | Lines 173–182 and lines 1016–1025 — the second adds `position: relative` (necessary for actions overlay), but is a maintenance risk |
| `--sp-7`, `--sp-9` missing | The spacing scale jumps `--sp-6 → --sp-8` and `--sp-8 → --sp-10`, leaving gaps |
| `font-size: inherit` on inputs in reset.css, then explicitly set to `14px` | Minor specificity mismatch |
| `mobile-back-btn` class applied in Header.jsx but not defined anywhere in CSS | Class name exists in JSX, no corresponding CSS rule found |

### UI Drift

| Area | Drift |
|---|---|
| Mobile content padding | `layout.css` sets `88px` bottom, `components.css @media` overrides to `24px` for the same selectors (`.overview-content`, `.section-content`, `.detail-content`) — conflict |
| Header breadcrumb depth 2 | Uses inline `style={{}}` instead of a CSS class for the back-to-section button in detail view |
| `share-modal-body gap` | Uses raw `20px` instead of `--sp-5` |
| `pwd-reset-confirm gap` | Uses `12px` instead of `--sp-3` |
| Overview edit button | Uses inline `style={{ flex:1, minWidth:0 }}` on Overview.jsx wrapper |

---

## 10. 🧠 FINAL SUMMARY

### Design System Identity

> **"Quiet Precision"** — A terminal-dark, information-focused UI with an extremely restrained palette, sharp geometry, and progressive disclosure navigation.

### What Style This Represents

| Trait | Description |
|---|---|
| **Theme** | Deep dark (`#0c0c0c` base) — not black, but near-obsidian |
| **Mood** | Developer-credential / portfolio tool — focused, document-like |
| **Accent** | Warm amber (`#b8956a`) — gives humanity/warmth to an otherwise cold dark UI |
| **Shape** | Brutalist-adjacent — square corners, 1px uniform borders, no shadows |
| **Density** | Medium-low — generous vertical padding on rows (16px), comfortable to scan |
| **Motion** | Subtle & intentional — spring easing on forward navigation, linear on back |

### What Is Working Well ✅

- **Token architecture is solid** — all background, border, and text relationships are properly tokenized
- **Typography hierarchy is clear** — 6 visual levels of text from 26px display down to 9px label caps
- **Spacing is consistent** — almost all padding/margin uses `--sp-*` tokens
- **Animation system is elegant** — directional transitions (in from right, out to right) create a natural spatial model
- **Responsive breakpoints** — both `640px` (mobile) and `380px` (xs) are handled thoughtfully
- **Component API is clean** — all components receive props with no internal state drift
- **Icon system is singular** — only Lucide React, consistent stroke, no library mixing
- **Row pattern is consistent** — all three row types (section, item, link) follow identical visual grammar

### What Is Inconsistent / Needs Attention ⚠️

| Priority | Issue |
|---|---|
| High | Error/success colors are hardcoded everywhere — need `--color-error`, `--color-success`, `--color-error-dim`, `--color-danger-border` tokens |
| High | Two CSS selectors duplicated (`.section-heading`, `.item-row`) — risk of drift |
| Medium | Mobile bottom padding conflict between `layout.css` and `components.css` — one wins, one is dead code |
| Medium | Three unused tokens (`--text-inverse`, `--radius-sm`, `--transition-slow`) — dead weight |
| Medium | Several hardcoded hex values inside tokenized contexts — should all be `var()` |
| Low | Missing spacing scale steps (`--sp-7`, `--sp-9`) — minor but causes raw pixel fallbacks |
| Low | `mobile-back-btn` class applied in JSX but undefined in CSS — may cause issues if that class is ever needed for mobile targeting |

---

